{"type":"message","id":"828c4254","parentId":"390b5204","timestamp":"2026-04-28T08:04:41.546Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gmail has no new emails in the last hour. Let me check iCloud - the envelope list shows 4 emails but I need to check if they're NEW (not already read). Looking at the flags, some have \"R\" (read) and \"!\" (flagged). Let me check the himalaya account to understand the date filter. The cron is for \"newer_than:1h\" so I should check if these iCloud emails are from the last hour. The most recent one is from 2026-04-27 19:06+00:00, which is about 13 hours ago, not within the last hour.\n\nWait, let me re-read the instructions. The cron job says to check both Gmail AND iCloud for new emails. For Gmail, the search is `newer_than:1h`. For iCloud, I should probably also check for recent emails. The himalaya list shows emails from April 27 and earlier - none from today (April 28). \n\nSince it's 4:04 AM on April 28 and the most recent iCloud email is from April 27 at 19:06 UTC (about 13 hours old), there don't appear to be any new emails in either inbox within the last hour. The Gmail search returned no results, and while there are 4 iCloud emails, they're all from yesterday or earlier. Let me send the notifications accordingly.","thinkingSignature":"c4b8e216ceaa494833a982e7edbe37428caa8f7b4ac6a91006497f3017402fe0"},{"type":"text","text":"📬 **GMAIL** — No new emails\n\n📬 **ICLOUD** — No new emails\n\n(Gmail: 0 new in last hour. iCloud: 4 emails total, most recent from Apr 27 ~13h ago — none new in last hour.)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":957,"output":353,"cacheRead":19036,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20346,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777363469532,"responseId":"063f9d0d9dc3a1f65cd78ba898b7240f"}}
